```class Solution {
public:
    string breakPalindrome(string palindrome) {
        int n = palindrome.size();
        if (n == 1) return "";
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            if (palindrome[i] != 'a') {
                palindrome[i] = 'a';
                return palindrome;
            }
        }
        palindrome[n - 1] = 'b';
        return palindrome;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the first half of the palindrome, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a' to make the lexicographically smallest non-palindrome. If all characters are 'a', it replaces the last character with 'b' to make it non-palindromic.

